% VisTools.% Version 2.0b        4 Mar 2001% Handy utility functions for doing some basic tasks.% Lawrence K. Cormack and Scott B. Stevenson, 1997-2002% *** indicates I've updated the help/header%% 1-D function generators.%***	dog			- Difference of gaussians.%***	gaus    	- Gaussian function.%***	gab			- 1D gabor function.%***	simpStim	- simple pulse function%***	tImpResp	- bi- or monophasic temporal impulse response function%% 2- and 3-D image generators.%***	buff2arr	- 1D buffer to array conversion.%***	ggaus		- 2D guassian distribution.%***	ddog		- 2D difference of gaussians (eq. area)%***	ggab		- 2D gabor function.%***	spike		- gives array in which amp=1/d^a, d = distance from origin%***    oneoverf    - makes a 1/f noise image%***    spike3d     - spike in a volume%***    oneoverf3d  - 1/f noise volume (i.e. movie)%***	cone		- amp. proportional to distance from edge%% Array manipulation.%***	roll		- Rolls (scrolls) rows down or up.%***	turn		- Turns (pans) columns left or right.%***	shift		- scrolls and pans in one call%***	shear   	- successively offsets rows of an array%***	trim		- Trims an array on all sides%***	triml, %***	trimt,%***	trimr,%***	trimb		-Trims l,t,r,or b of an array by specified amount%% Image display and gamma correction%	showim		- displays an image somewhat sensibly%	graylut		- makes a gray ramp lut of specified length%	gammainv	- makes a gamma-corrected ramp LUT%	gammamap	- gamma corrects an existing LUT%	lintest		- quick visual verification of LUT linearity%	sky			- blue to white colormap%	splitCMap	- red-to-green map with break at the data's zero%% Image and movie related.%	one2ff		- norms [-1 1] data to uint8 data in range [0 255].%	bumpup		- bumps [-1 1] data up to [0 1].%***	coswin		- make a circular window with cosine taper%	cosbar		- elongated window with cosine cross-section%	filtnoise	- return noise filtered with a provided kernel%	oneoverf	- returns 1/f^a noise%	halfwave	- half-wave rectifies %	invert		- reverses the contrast about the dc level%	subpix		- subpixel image shift via linear interpolation%% Analysis%	normalize	- Normalizes elements (default range = [0-1]).%	killdc		- subtracts the average value%	filtresp	- computes static response of linear spatial filter%	ssum		- sums across all dimensions (i.e. an overall sum)%	mmax 		- overall max of an array%	mmin		- guess%	aave		- guess again%	geomean		- computes the geometric mean%	linefit		- Fits a straight line to x,y data%***   sinFit      - Fits a single cycle sinusoid to a data vector%	ttest		- t-test on an Nx2 data matrix%	isodd		- tests for odd%	iseven		- tests for even%% Conversion%***	d2r			- converts degrees to radians%***	r2d			- converts radians to degrees%***	pix2deg		- converts pixels to degrees%***	deg2pix		- converts degrees to pixels%	sig2bw		- gaussian space constant to octave bandwidth%	bw2sig		- bandwidth (octaves) to gaussian space constant%	disp2blur	- retinal disparity (arcmin) to defocus (diopters)%% Miscellanious graphix%	addErrBars	- add error bars to plots and bar charts%	cls			- clears all windows created by SCREEN()	%	unitcirc	- returns n points around the unit circle%	cutlines	- removes nappy gridlines from volumetric slice plots%	xscale		- rescales x-axis of plots%	yscale		- ditto for y-axis%